              <span id="reviewTextContainer2254035706" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9641203252750132655"><strong>Insightful read for everyone - not just ecologists!</strong><br/><br/>Books written by scientists are not always page turners, but this book is an exception. I thoroughly enjoyed the author&apos;s mixture of stories and data to illustrate fascinating conclusions about why animals have weapons. The parallels drawn between the military history of humans and the animal kingdom are very enlightening. I highly recommend this book!</span>
  <span id="freeText9641203252750132655" style="display:none"><strong>Insightful read for everyone - not just ecologists!</strong><br /><br />Books written by scientists are not always page turners, but this book is an exception. I thoroughly enjoyed the author's mixture of stories and data to illustrate fascinating conclusions about why animals have weapons. The parallels drawn between the military history of humans and the animal kingdom are very enlightening. I highly recommend this book!</span>
