<div id="review_1754174386" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1754174386" />
    <a title="Paul" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10108659-paul"><img alt="Paul" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1339283766p2/10108659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1754174386?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Paul" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Paul" href="/user/show/10108659-paul">Paul</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1754174386" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1268203786989827900">That Doug Emlen sure can write. He distills a whole bunch of evolutionary theory down into understandable prose, offers great natural history case studies and a little lab science to bolster his story, weaves in charming personal anecdotes, and draws out the parallels between arms races in the animal and human worlds without too much straining. Plus he has a great illustrator. Whew!</span>

          </span>
        </div>


